# Styling Conventions

## SCSS Modules + Tailwind (Standard)

- ALL component styles in `<ComponentName>.module.scss`
- Every SCSS module MUST start with `@reference` to access Tailwind:

```scss
@reference "tailwindcss/theme";
@reference "tailwindcss/utilities";

.root {
  @apply flex flex-col items-center p-4 gap-2;
}
```

- Import in component: `import styles from './ComponentName.module.scss'`

## Tailwind is the Single Source of Truth

ALL layout/spacing/sizing/typography values come from Tailwind via `@apply` or `var(--spacing-*)`.
ALL colors come from Primer CSS custom properties via `var(--fgColor-*)`, `var(--bgColor-*)`.
NEVER create custom SCSS token files.

### What Goes Where

| Need | Approach |
|------|----------|
| Layout, flexbox, grid | `@apply flex`, `@apply grid`, etc. |
| Spacing (padding, gap) | `@apply p-4 gap-2` or `var(--spacing-4)` |
| Sizing (w, h, min/max) | `@apply w-full min-h-screen` |
| Colors (Primer) | `var(--fgColor-default)`, `var(--bgColor-muted)` |
| Typography | `@apply text-sm font-semibold` |
| Borders / radius | `@apply rounded-md border` |
| Shadows | `@apply shadow-sm` |
| Complex / stateful styles | SCSS with `var(--spacing-*)`, Primer `var()` |

### Example: Mixed Usage

```scss
@reference "tailwindcss/theme";
@reference "tailwindcss/utilities";

.root {
  @apply flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 rounded-lg;
}

.default {
  color: var(--fgColor-default);
  background-color: var(--bgColor-default);
}

.highlighted {
  background-color: var(--bgColor-accent-muted);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--borderColor-accent-emphasis);
}
```

## Colors — Primer CSS Custom Properties

Colors come from Primer's `ThemeProvider` at runtime as CSS custom properties.
Use `var(--fgColor-default)`, `var(--bgColor-muted)`, `var(--borderColor-default)`, etc. directly in SCSS.
NEVER use hex, rgb, hsl, or named colors directly.

## Zero Inline JS Styles

- NEVER use the `style` prop — PROHIBITED
- NEVER use `sx`, `css`, or any JS-in-CSS approach
- ALL styling via `className` internally

## No className as Prop — Variant Only

Components NEVER accept `className`, `style`, or any styling-related prop.
The ONLY way to alter appearance is via a typed `variant` prop.

```tsx
import styles from './Card.module.scss'

export const Card = ({ variant, children }: CardProps) => (
  <div className={`${styles.root} ${styles[variant]}`}>
    {children}
  </div>
)
```

## No Margin — Ever

NEVER use `margin` in any form. Use `padding` or `gap`.
Enforced by Stylelint `property-disallowed-list`.
